CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1952, pg. 1, reads: "Everybody Liked 'Gus' - The ordinary people, the little folk, and the big ones with power and influence liked William A. (Gus) Greenlee, who died at his home here Monday after being ill for the past two years. Men, women, and children displayed it in same manner that this customer at the now burned-out Crawford Grill is showing in this photo... Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Gus Greenlee with arm around woman, standing in Crawford Grill No. 1
